item.title: Sequence Analysis- What It Is and How to Do It
item.description:
Sequence analysis is a technique used in longitudinal research to understand developmental trajectories. I will briefly cover the main goals of this technique and sample code of how to conduct analyses, but for an in depth discussion of the methodology and examples of sequence-type research questions, I'd recommend you browse through the TraMineR R package user guide.
